  "Description": "The Start goal initiates a series of tests to verify the functionality of isolated goal calls in the Plang programming environment. It begins by announcing the start of the tests, then proceeds to execute three distinct tests. The first test checks if a normal call can access shared variables, the second test verifies the execution of an isolated goal, and the third test assesses the functionality of an isolated call with a parameter by writing to and reading from a file. The goal concludes by summarizing the results of the tests and noting a known issue with isolated calls.",
